      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HEEZ A VIBE (8) settled well back last start and saluted by 2 metres, in a far better performance at this track over 1800m. Shouldn't spend a penny from this draw and the sprint lane may come in handy. Meets some better types this time but he has the ability to make it two on the trot. NICKS PICK (6) settled in the leading division the went to the front and closed the race off well to win for the second time in a row last start over 1609m at Port Pirie, getting there by 5 metres. A big run is on the cards. DON ARTHUR (7) is right in the mix after finishing runner-up for the second time in a row last start, beaten 4.5 metres at this course. Ideally placed to go one better. SUNSTAR (4) is worth some thought based on his third over 1609m at Port Pirie two runs ago. One for the exotics players.",
